# Git & Delivery (Always)

## Commits

- Create commits **only** when the user explicitly asks
- Never update git config
- Never `--no-verify` / skip hooks unless user explicitly asks
- No force push to main/master; warn if requested
- Amend only under the user’s amend rules (explicit ask or hook-auto-modify of *your* unpushed commit)
- If commit fails hooks: fix + **new** commit (never amend a failed commit)
- Commit message via HEREDOC; use caveman-commit skill when committing
- Never commit `.env`, secrets, credential files

## Pull requests

- Only when user asks; use `gh`; follow user PR checklist (status, diff, log, then push + `gh pr create`)

## Push

- Never push unless user explicitly asks
- **After every commit+push that touches API/server (or when user says ship):** also deploy EC2 API — do not leave “redeploy later.” Prefer GitHub Action `deploy-api.yml` (auto on `server/**` / `deploy/**` push to `main`); if Action fails or user asks now, SSH and run `bash ~/AIIMIN/deploy/github-ec2-deploy.sh` (host `13.207.146.15`, key `~/Desktop/aiimin.pem` or repo `aiimin.pem`). Verify `https://api.aiimin.in/api/health` and SHA matches push.
- Frontend: Vercel auto-deploys from `main`; confirm READY when shipping.

## Done means

Code change + vault update (MOC/changelog/manifest/Current Context as needed) in the same unit of work — not “docs later”. When user asked to push, EC2 (API) is part of done too.
